content.description: start in the middle of the face and work up about 15ft before traversing right around the arete then up the slab
content.location: the broken seam just right of Booboo kitty

content.description:
Right crack of a dual crack dihedral running up one of the small columns protruding from the Northeast face.  Starts with fingers and hand jams; moves into lieback; finishes with offwidth. 

 Tree anchor is to the left of column approximately 50% up the entire Northeast face.

 Note: using the offwidth left crack in addition to the right for hands would drop the grade.
content.protection:
Gear used to sew it up (in approximate order): BD 0.75 (green), BD 0.5 (purple), BD #1 (red), BD #1 (red), BD #2 (orange), BD #3 (blue), T 0.5 (black), M MasterCam #8 (purple).

 Notes: The offwidth section near the top has a small horizontal pocket for a BD #3 (or a M #8 like I used).

 A BD 0.4(gray), an extra BD #2, and a BD #6 might be useful for some.

 Anchor: Two 1" webbing with rap ring to the left of route around tree (forgive the neon color: I hope that this is temporary).

 BD = Black Diamond M = Metolius T = Totem
content.location: Approximately in the middle of Northeast formation.  Around 7 columns to the right of the "phalanges" looking formation (see pic).

content.description: The big offwidth to the righ of Booboo kitty
content.protection: Gear to 6in and possible Big Bro placemants
content.location: Start behind a small tree in the obvious dihedral

content.description: find the obvious notch in the cliff then head right about 100 yards until you pass the trail that accesses the top of the cliff, continue past the trail for about 20 ft until you see the line. It stands out from the other more pure lines around it. It starts with perfect hands then switches to fists then offwidth
content.protection: set of cams from .75-2 and doubles of 3-5

content.description: while approaching you will see an obvious notch in the middle of the cliff, the columns to the right are the north east routes, to the left are the south east routes
